/stack traces from CLI code\\n   146→- Checkpoint metadata structurally corrupt (malformed JSON, missing `checkpoint_id`/`strategy`)\\n   147→- Session state file missing or malformed when expected\\n   148→- Hooks did not fire at all (no `hook invoked` log entries)\\n   149→- Shadow/metadata branch has wrong tree structure\\n   150→- Same test fails across 3+ agents with same non-timeout symptom\\n   151→- Error references CLI code (panic in `cmd/entire/cli/`)\\n   152→\\n   153→**Key question:** Is the bug in `cmd/entire/cli/` (product code) or in `e2e/` (test code)? Only the former is a `real-bug`.\\n   154→\\n   155→#### Strong `flaky` signals (unless overridden by real-bug):\\n   156→\\n   157→**Agent behavior (non-deterministic):**\\n   158→- `signal: killed` (timeout)\\n   159→- `context deadline exceeded` or `WaitForCheckpoint.*exceeded deadline`\\n   160→- Agent asked for confirmation instead of acting\\n   161→- Agent created file at wrong path / wrong name\\n   162→- Agent produced no output\\n   163→- Agent committed when it shouldn't have (or vice versa)\\n   164→- Duration near timeout limit\\n   165→\\n   166→**Test-bug (consistent failure, but root cause is in `e2e/` not `cmd/entire/cli/`):**\\n   167→- Agent \\\"Not logged in\\\" / auth errors → test env setup doesn't propagate auth credentials\\n   168→- Env vars not propagated to agent session → tmux/test harness bug\\n   169→- Error references test code (`e2e/`) not CLI code (`cmd/entire/cli/`)\\n   170→- Test helper logic errors (wrong assertions, bad globs, incorrect expected values)\\n   171→- Consistent failure BUT root cause traced to `e2e/` code, not `cmd/entire/cli/`\\n   172→- Test setup/teardown issues (missing git config, temp dir cleanup, port conflicts)\\n   173→\\n   174→#### Ambiguous cases:\\n   175→\\n   176→Read `entire.log` carefully:\\n   177→- If hooks fired correctly and metadata is valid -> lean **flaky**\\n   178→- If hooks fired but produced wrong results -> lean **real-bug**\\n   179→\\n   180→### Step 3: Cross-Agent Correlation\\n   181→\\n   182→Before acting, check correlations using re-run data:\\n   183→- Same test fails for 3+ agents, all re-runs also fail -> strong **real-bug**\\n   184→- Same test fails for multiple agents, but re-runs pass -> **flaky** (shared prompt issue)\\n   185→- One agent fails consistently, others pass -> agent-specific issue (still **real-bug** if re-runs confirm)\\n   186→\\n   187→### Step 4a: Take Action — Local Mode\\n   188→\\n   189→In local mode, present findings interactively. **Do not** create branches, PRs, or GitHub issues.\\n   190→\\n   191→#### Present Findings Report\\n   192→\\n   193→For each test+agent pair, print a findings block:\\n   194→\\n   195→```\\n   196→## <TestName> (<agent>) — <classification>\\n   197→\\n   198→**Re-run results:** original=FAIL, rerun1=PASS, rerun2=PASS\\n   199→**Evidence:**\\n   200→- <1-2 sentence summary of what went wrong>\\n   201→- <key artifact evidence: entire.log excerpt, console.log excerpt, etc.>\\n   202→```\\n   203→\\n   204→#### For `flaky` failures: describe the proposed fix\\n   205→\\n   206→For agent-behavior flaky issues, fixes typically modify test prompts. For test-bug flaky issues, fixes target `e2e/` infrastructure code (harness setup, helpers, env propagation).\\n   207→\\n   208→```\\n   209→**Proposed fix:** <description>\\n   210→  - File: <path to test file or e2e infrastructure file>\\n   211→  - Change: <what will be modified — e.g., append \\\"Do not ask for confirmation\\\" to prompt, or fix env propagation in NewTmuxSession>\\n   212→```\\n   213→\\n   214→Common flaky fixes (same as CI mode):\\n   215→- Agent asked for confirmation -> append \\\"Do not ask for confirmation\\\" to prompt\\n   216→- Agent wrote to wrong path -> be more explicit about paths in prompt\\n   217→- Agent committed when shouldn't -> add \\\"Do not commit\\\" to prompt\\n   218→- Checkpoint wait timeout -> increase timeout argument\\n   219→- Agent timeout (signal: killed) -> increase per-test timeout, simplify prompt\\n   220→- Auth/env not propagated -> fix test harness env setup in `e2e/` code\\n   221→- Test helper bug (wrong assertion, bad glob) -> fix test helper in `e2e/`\\n   222→- tmux session setup issue -> fix `NewTmuxSession` or session config in `e2e/`\\n   223→\\n   224→#### For `real-bug` failures: describe root cause analysis\"}]},\"uuid\":\"c0d05b5b-a14d-4a38-9f3b-15f20f3bf16a\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-06T22:28:36.877Z\",\"toolUseResult\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"file\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/cli/.claude/skills/e2e-triage/SKILL.md\",\"content\":\"### Step 2: Classify Each Failure\\n\\nUse **re-run results as the primary signal**, supplemented by artifact analysis.\\n\\n#### Re-run signals (strongest):\\n\\n| Original | Re-run 1 | Re-run 2 | Classification |\\n|----------|----------|----------|----------------|\\n| FAIL | FAIL (same error) | FAIL (same error) | **real-bug** OR **flaky (test-bug)** — see below |\\n| FAIL | PASS | PASS | **flaky** |\\n| FAIL | PASS | FAIL | **flaky** (non-deterministic) |\\n| FAIL | FAIL | PASS | **flaky** (non-deterministic) |\\n| FAIL | FAIL (different error) | FAIL (different error) | **needs deeper analysis** — examine artifacts |\\n\\n**Important: Consistent failures can still be `flaky` (test-bug).** When all re-runs fail, check *where* the root cause is:\\n- Root cause in `cmd/entire/cli/` → **real-bug** (product code is broken)\\n- Root cause in `e2e/` (test infra, test helpers, tmux setup, env propagation) → **flaky (test-bug)** — the CLI works fine, the test is broken\\n\\n#### Strong `real-bug` signals (root cause must be in `cmd/entire/cli/`, not `e2e/`):\\n\\n- `entire.log` contains `\\\"level\\\":\\\"ERROR\\\"` or panic/stack traces from CLI code\\n- Checkpoint metadata structurally corrupt (malformed JSON, missing `checkpoint_id`/`strategy`)\\n- Session state file missing or malformed when expected\\n- Hooks did not fire at all (no `hook invoked` log entries)\\n- Shadow/metadata branch has wrong tree structure\\n- Same test fails across 3+ agents with same non-timeout symptom\\n- Error references CLI code (panic in `cmd/entire/cli/`)\\n\\n**Key question:** Is the bug in `cmd/entire/cli/` (product code) or in `e2e/` (test code)? Only the former is a `real-bug`.\\n\\n#### Strong `flaky` signals (unless overridden by real-bug):\\n\\n**Agent behavior (non-deterministic):**\\n- `signal: killed` (timeout)\\n- `context deadline exceeded` or `WaitForCheckpoint.*exceeded deadline`\\n- Agent asked for confirmation instead of acting\\n- Agent created file at wrong path / wrong name\\n- Agent produced no output\\n- Agent committed when it shouldn't have (or vice versa)\\n- Duration near timeout limit\\n\\n**Test-bug (consistent failure, but root cause is in `e2e/` not `cmd/entire/cli/`):**\\n- Agent \\\"Not logged in\\\" / auth errors → test env setup doesn't propagate auth credentials\\n- Env vars not propagated to agent session → tmux/test harness bug\\n- Error references test code (`e2e/`) not CLI code (`cmd/entire/cli/`)\\n- Test helper logic errors (wrong assertions, bad globs, incorrect expected values)\\n- Consistent failure BUT root cause traced to `e2e/` code, not `cmd/entire/cli/`\\n- Test setup/teardown issues (missing git config, temp dir cleanup, port conflicts)\\n\\n#### Ambiguous cases:\\n\\nRead `entire.log` carefully:\\n- If hooks fired correctly and metadata is valid -> lean **flaky**\\n- If hooks fired but produced wrong results -> lean **real-bug**\\n\\n### Step 3: Cross-Agent Correlation\\n\\nBefore acting, check correlations using re-run data:\\n- Same test fails for 3+ agents, all re-runs also fail -> strong **real-bug**\\n- Same test fails for multiple agents, but re-runs pass -> **flaky** (shared prompt issue)\\n- One agent fails consistently, others pass -> agent-specific issue (still **real-bug** if re-runs confirm)\\n\\n### Step 4a: Take Action — Local Mode\\n\\nIn local mode, present findings interactively. **Do not** create branches, PRs, or GitHub issues.\\n\\n#### Present Findings Report\\n\\nFor each test+agent pair, print a findings block:\\n\\n```\\n## <TestName> (<agent>) — <classification>\\n\\n**Re-run results:** original=FAIL, rerun1=PASS, rerun2=PASS\\n**Evidence:**\\n- <1-2 sentence summary of what went wrong>\\n- <key artifact evidence: entire.log excerpt, console.log excerpt, etc.>\\n```\\n\\n#### For `flaky` failures: describe the proposed fix\\n\\nFor agent-behavior flaky issues, fixes typically modify test prompts. For test-bug flaky issues, fixes target `e2e/` infrastructure code (harness setup, helpers, env propagation).\\n\\n```\\n**Proposed fix:** <description>\\n  - File: <path to test file or e2e infrastructure file>\\n  - Change: <what will be modified — e.g., append \\\"Do not ask for confirmation\\\" to prompt, or fix env propagation in NewTmuxSession>\\n```\\n\\nCommon flaky fixes (same as CI mode):\\n- Agent asked for confirmation -> append \\\"Do not ask for confirmation\\\" to prompt\\n- Agent wrote to wrong path -> be more explicit about paths in prompt\\n- Agent committed when shouldn't -> add \\\"Do not commit\\\" to prompt\\n- Checkpoint wait timeout -> increase timeout argument\\n- Agent timeout (signal: killed) -> increase per-test timeout, simplify prompt\\n- Auth/env not propagated -> fix test harness env setup in `e2e/` code\\n- Test helper bug (wrong assertion, bad glob) -> fix test helper in `e2e/`\\n- tmux session setup issue -> fix `NewTmuxSession` or session config in `e2e/`\\n\\n#### For `real-bug` failures: describe root cause analysis\",\"numLines\":100,\"startLine\":125,\"totalLines\":369}},\"sourceToolAssistantUUID\":\"1e99f28c-bb94-4233-9858-21d891176d88\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"c0d05b5b-a14d-4a38-9f3b-15f20f3bf16a\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"43151417-d46e-4428-9677-d17ed2bc6ee6\",\"version\":\"2.1.